# structure:
# 1. player creates a room:
# 2. player joins a room:
# 3. player votes to go either solo or with team mate to decide to set the challenge:
# --- mutual vote =true if both agrees:
# --- solo set =true if one of the player disagrees:
# 4. player than toss:
# ------ toss session over:
# 5. player set the challenge:
# 6. game begins:
# 7.round format: round robin best of 2
# per set there are two rounds:
# set match-up:
# set 1:
# R1:
# 0v0:
# R2:
# 1v1:
# set 2:
# R1:
# 1v0:
# R2:
# 0v1:
# set 3:
# R1:
# 1v1:
# R2:
# 0v0:

# rules:
# 1. display team details broadcast syntax: team your_name
# example: team red // valid
#          teamRed // invalid
#          team_RED // invalid too
# 2. the token came from client to be converted into upper-cases:

# ### if you the go coroutine is not working properly it means that either you have not set the sync's method correctly or not able to add the chan in the hub
# ### prohibition of global words:
# ### token, id, r

# ### dictionary-folder:
# fetches the events from the database:
# ### books-folder:
# fetches the books from the sse database:
# ## server-folder:
# broadcasts to the client :

# ### books is broadcast only one single book as per the created room
# ### dictionary[event] is broadcast on the basis of the book
# ### events[participants country or any] are broadcast on the basis of the dictionary
# ### connected to main database

# # locify mode:---------------
# # basically we lock players into two teams
# # where they face each other as a team

# # clash mode:----------------
# # we lock players into two teams
# # where they each other in a stored team

# # events updating
# the game does the things in simple:
# _for locify it will store :
#       1. count_of_category: category of the room in which player played
#       2. count_of_all_points: total points earned in the match by the player
#       3. count_of_all_the_used_powers: power-up's used by the player
#       4. count_of_all_the_result: counting only the winning result // #NOTE: note counting the 2nd place

# _for clash it will store:
#       1. count_of_category: category of the room in which player played
#       2. count_of_all_bosses: total times the player has become final boss in a match
#       3. count_of_all_the_used_powers: power-up's used by the player
#       4. count_of_all_the_result: counting only the winning result // #NOTE: note counting the 2nd place

